  "text": "C/D/C add/drop can be realized by combining splitters and switches, and is referred to as a multi-cast switch [CITATION_1] . To attain directionless add/drop functions, however, signals must be distributed/aggregated to/from all the receivers/transmitters by using large-degree splitters [CITATION_2] . Therefore, this configuration requires a large number of erbium-doped-fiber amplifiers (EDFAs) to compensate the large splitter loss. Furthermore, large-scale 1 Â n switches are necessary to create a multi-cast switch that can select a target fiber out of many input or output fibers.",
